# Frontend rules

## Components

- Every UI surface is a Nuxt component in `app/components/` (Sidebar, AppHeader, CommitGraph, etc.).
- Reuse `XTerm.vue` for any embedded terminal — do not duplicate xterm/WebSocket logic.
- Commit graph layout lives in `app/utils/graph.ts`; keep SVG rendering in `CommitGraph.vue`.

## State (Pinia)

| Store | Role |
|-------|------|
| `projects` | Sidebar list, selected project, add/remove |
| `repo` | Git data for active project (log, branches, status, staging) |
| `ui` | Terminal open, GitHub setup modal |

Load repo data when `projects.selected.path` changes (`app/app.vue` watcher).

## Styling

- Dark GitKraken-inspired palette: `ink-*`, `accent` (see `tailwind.config.ts`).
- Utility classes: `.btn-primary`, `.btn-ghost`, `.btn-subtle`, `.input` in `app/assets/css/main.css`.
- No inline style sprawl — prefer Tailwind utilities.

## API calls

- Use `$fetch` to `/api/git/*`, `/api/projects/*`, `/api/gh/*`.
- WIP / uncommitted row uses `WIP` constant from `stores/repo.ts`.
